  "commentary": "**DEALER HEDGING COMMENTARY:**\n\nWith SPX at 6780.2 sitting just below the GEX flip at 6782, dealers are in long gamma mode and will aggressively sell any push toward the massive 6800 gamma wall (62.7B). The wall break and GEX surge events indicate dealers just absorbed heavy flow, likely from the sharp move that triggered rebalancing into these key strikes. Watch 6785-6800 as the primary resistance zone where dealer selling intensifies, while 6770 represents the downside support level where dealers flip to buying.\n\n**Bottom line:** Expect price to get pinned between 6770-6800 with dealers acting as stabilizers.",
